	   <tr><td colspan=2>...than reply to the above post.<br><br>As it is mentioned already on this page a few times, you don't quest for the headbands to wear them you need them as pre-quests for the monk epic.<br><br>Sure, I only have  24th Iksar monk who has Orange Headband and Orange Sash so I can't talk about how great it is have &lt;insert uber item name here&gt; and what not but I've enjoyed spending quite a bit (slight understatement) of time on faction.  I can bank and train in Freeport (Dubious with pallies and militia, and Ally with monks), I can bank in Highkeep (dubiously), I can buy/sell in the warrior guild in Kelethin (banker is not on work-able faction), I am dubious with the guards in Butcher Block.  I got some RL friends of mine who have leveled their chars higher and faster, however, they seemed to be having little fun with EQ.<br><br>Everquest was meant as a Roleplaying Game.  If you can't roleplay you are missing out on A LOT.  I can't change how most people act but I don't need to listen to rants (*sigh* even like mine) abotu how the stats on this; suck, blow, are worthless, etc... I personally wear my Orange Sash with pride knowing that I didn't just make a monk in Freeport and/or Qeynos for the sole purpose of the quests.<br><br>As for  the info you seek, try looking up the quest for the red headband.  That is the quest that takes you to South Karana after the Gnoll High Shamans.  Or if you are after information on Epic, RotWF, RotLC, and such try going here...<br><br><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles.asp?ArticleId=1" target=_new>http://www.monkly-business.com/articles.asp?ArticleId=1</a><br><br>Sorry to to those who like me don't like rants.  Hopefully atleast have some constructive info puts this on top of most of the other near-pointless rants.<br><br>/emote sighs and walks towards zone edge.<br><br>Zebulian Retired/Canabalized 19th Ranger of Povar<br>   Master Fletcher<br>Ztix 24th Iksar Monk of Povar<br>  