	   <tr><td colspan=2>Amen.  It is possible for iksar to get the red sash and purple headband by killing the monk trainers, for people who don't care about making nice with the humans, which I think is good from a realistic rolelaying perspective, having an alternate method for people who want to roleplay their iksar that way.  I personally prefer to play my monk as a "tourist," who doesn't mind killing low level creatures or preforming menail tasks to get on people's good side.  I worked up my Ashen Order faction by "faction borrowing," went to the orc camps and gave a weak kick to each of the orcs people were camping there to get the faction without stealing their kills.  Sometimes I'd take on the entire WC orc camp by myself, as that one doesn't seem to be camped very often, at least not on my server.<br><br>Still need to work on Silent Fist.  I've killed so many gnolls that my faction with them can't get any worse and my faction with non-corrupt guards is amiable, but I still only have dubious faction with the monks.  Well, more time in Blackburrow it looks like.<br><br>I currently can bank in Freeport, Rivervale, and Qeynos.  And I can walk through Butcherblock without being hassled by the dwarf guards.  I plan on working on other cities, but want to get my red sash before moving on.  Ekeros shouldn't be too hard to camp, although Befallen looks to be a pain.  But it's worth the effort.<br>&nbsp;<br>Troodon, AKA Zararazu, Level 38 Iksar Monk, Jaggedpine Defender, Solusek Ro</td></tr>
